1
00:00:-4,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>Good Doctor</i>

2
00:00:01,250 --> 00:00:03,380
<i> Episode 16 </i>

3
00:00:13,230 --> 00:00:15,600
Who are you?

4
00:00:18,340 --> 00:00:21,350
Yeong Seo. Yeong Seo.

5
00:00:22,550 --> 00:00:25,620
Doc. It's that guy.

6
00:00:25,620 --> 00:00:27,210
That guy!

7
00:00:27,210 --> 00:00:31,910
Are you the guy who made her like that?

8
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:36,520
Mister, you are really a bad guy!

9
00:00:36,520 --> 00:00:40,580
Y... y... you are truly a bad guy!

10
00:00:51,170 --> 00:00:52,870
Take Yeong Seo and leave!

11
00:00:52,870 --> 00:00:53,520
Professor.

12
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:55,810
Hurry, Park Si On!

13
00:01:01,890 --> 00:01:04,650
Help please! Help!

14
00:02:08,810 --> 00:02:10,660
Professor!

15
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:15,280
Professor.

16
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:31,140
What have we here?

17
00:02:31,850 --> 00:02:37,210
If you get on your knees right now, I'll at least let you live.

18
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:41,750
If you do anything stupid...

19
00:02:41,750 --> 00:02:43,900
Then you're going to die.

20
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:47,920
Did you get it, you bastard?

21
00:02:49,950 --> 00:02:53,050
Come to your senses, Professor!

22
00:02:59,110 --> 00:03:01,630
Are you all right?

23
00:03:01,630 --> 00:03:04,620
Don't make such a fuss, I'm fine.

24
00:03:04,620 --> 00:03:05,730
How is his condition?

25
00:03:05,730 --> 00:03:08,420
According to the results of the examination,
fortunately, there's no damage to the organs.

26
00:03:08,420 --> 00:03:12,450
The stab wound is slightly angled that there is only damage to the abdominal walls.

27
00:03:13,620 --> 00:03:16,730
It's really a relief. It could have been much worse.

28
00:03:16,730 --> 00:03:19,920
How could you jump in so recklessly?

29
00:03:21,850 --> 00:03:24,800
Dr. Park was more reckless than I was.

30
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:30,110
You were great, Park Si On.

31
00:03:34,150 --> 00:03:36,420
What about the culprit?

32
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,260
S... Senior Nurse!!

33
00:03:57,260 --> 00:04:00,250
You should have stayed at home instead of coming here.

34
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:04,450
No... What... What the heck happened?

35
00:04:04,450 --> 00:04:06,510
I'm sorry.

36
00:04:06,510 --> 00:04:09,410
For now, I think you need to go with him.

37
00:04:09,410 --> 00:04:12,630
But, he caught the culprit. Where do you have to take him like a criminal?

38
00:04:12,630 --> 00:04:16,100
It's okay. Let's go.

39
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:17,840
No. I'll go with you.

40
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:19,040
No, you can just stay here.

41
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:21,480
How can I just stay here?

42
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,940
Police Officer, let's go.

43
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:28,520
You are not hurt?
- No.

44
00:04:30,290 --> 00:04:32,600
Are you still shaking?

45
00:04:33,390 --> 00:04:38,240
It's the first time I ever hit someone.

46
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:41,010
How did it feel to hit someone?

47
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:47,550
When I saw heroes hit the villains in movies, it felt good.

48
00:04:47,550 --> 00:04:52,330
So, I thought I would feel good after hitting a bad person.

49
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:54,330
It isn't like that.

50
00:04:54,330 --> 00:04:56,920
There's something called unavoidable violence.

51
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:59,200
In a situation like today, I mean.

52
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:04,150
If no one took on that discord, we wouldn't
have been able to catch that criminal.

53
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:11,020
But you absolutely can not use violence
that's intentional or without reason.

54
00:05:11,020 --> 00:05:15,560
Your conduct today was appropriate.

55
00:05:18,650 --> 00:05:23,480
But you... What if, as I'm walking at night, I'm completely surrounded by gangsters...

56
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:26,620
What will you do? Will you stay still?

57
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,500
The thugs are trying to do something bad to me.

58
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:35,770
"Ah! What are you doing? What do I do?"
 You're the only one around. What will you do?

59
00:05:35,770 --> 00:05:37,710
This is what I'll do.

60
00:05:37,710 --> 00:05:39,810
What?

61
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:43,490
"How many cavities do you have?"

62
00:05:43,490 --> 00:05:44,370
What?

63
00:05:44,370 --> 00:05:47,050
"I run a pawnshop."

64
00:05:47,050 --> 00:05:49,770
"I accept gold crowns."

65
00:05:49,770 --> 00:05:55,890
"After pulling out the gold crowns, I'll chew you up."

66
00:05:55,890 --> 00:05:58,450
That's from the movie Ahjussi.

67
00:05:58,450 --> 00:06:01,440
What if that gangster has an implant?

68
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,650
(My thoughts) didn't go that far.

69
00:06:02,650 --> 00:06:05,540
Stop watching movies, please.

70
00:06:05,540 --> 00:06:09,030
That's when you're supposed to fight.

71
00:06:13,030 --> 00:06:15,310
With more power.

72
00:06:28,390 --> 00:06:30,640
How did you find out?

73
00:06:31,710 --> 00:06:34,770
Dr. Han told me.

74
00:06:34,770 --> 00:06:36,890
That kid. Needlessly.

75
00:06:36,890 --> 00:06:40,130
Do you always have to make me find out too late like this?

76
00:06:42,140 --> 00:06:44,050
I didn't want you to worry.

77
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:46,600
If I found out later,

78
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:50,450
you knew instead of worrying I would have been angry first.

79
00:06:50,450 --> 00:06:52,660
I'm sorry.

80
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:54,730
It's not a big deal.

81
00:06:54,730 --> 00:06:57,370
Then, what is considered a big deal?

82
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:02,100
If something bad happens to you,

83
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:04,870
have you thought about how I would feel?

84
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:13,750
I have a prayer I say.

85
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:18,490
Since God took my father and mother away early,

86
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:24,540
to allow the people I have left to stay with me for a long time.

87
00:07:26,150 --> 00:07:31,730
I don't know about other times, but
when it's a serious situation, think a bit about me.

88
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:37,510
I understand. I won't do it again.

89
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:44,530
I don't believe you. What you said.

90
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:11,350
Yeong Seo. Now you really don't have to be worried.

91
00:08:11,350 --> 00:08:13,170
Understand?

92
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:17,280
The bad guy was punished a lot.

93
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:19,450
By all of us.

94
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,220
Yeong Seo.

95
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:27,400
You have more good people than bad people next to you.

96
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:31,240
So, from now on you don't have to be worried.

97
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:34,730
Doctor.

98
00:08:34,730 --> 00:08:38,670
Is that doctor all right?

99
00:08:38,670 --> 00:08:42,030
Ah, the professor?

100
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,890
He's fine.

101
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:49,750
That doctor was like my dad.

102
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:51,710
My dad.

103
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:55,750
I see.

104
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:59,120
We'll be like your dad and uncle.

105
00:09:11,180 --> 00:09:13,180
Geez, they should say something that makes sense.

106
00:09:13,180 --> 00:09:15,840
When you caught the criminal for them,
what, excessive defense?

107
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:18,630
Well, that's what the law says. What can I do?

108
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:20,070
Don't worry.

109
00:09:20,070 --> 00:09:23,540
If they go on about punishment or something,
we'll take measures at the level of the association.

110
00:09:23,540 --> 00:09:26,600
I mean, where is another nurse like this?

111
00:09:27,460 --> 00:09:31,710
It's been a while since I've been questioned that I feel like my stomach is a little empty inside.

112
00:09:31,710 --> 00:09:35,200
Wh... wh... what do you want?

113
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,940
Meat?

114
00:09:43,770 --> 00:09:45,140
But, Senior Nurse.

115
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:46,250
Yes?

116
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:48,550
How did you fight so well?

117
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:50,350
Especially with someone wielding a knife.

118
00:09:50,350 --> 00:09:52,030
Well, it just happened.

119
00:09:52,030 --> 00:09:53,620
Do you have a black belt or something?

120
00:09:53,620 --> 00:09:57,430
No, I just used my fists some around
the neighborhood in the old days.

121
00:09:57,790 --> 00:10:00,090
Even then...

122
00:10:01,790 --> 00:10:06,310
I... have something I am suddenly curious of.

123
00:10:06,310 --> 00:10:08,040
What is it?

124
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,990
Because earlier, when you were writing the report, I saw

125
00:10:09,990 --> 00:10:12,390
the two Chinese characters for "Joeng Mi" from your name Jo Jeong Mi,

126
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:15,850
they were the same Chinese characters used to spell rice mill (jeong-mi-so). What does your name mean?

127
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:17,450
You're right. They are the characters
used to spell rice mill.

128
00:10:17,470 --> 00:10:18,940
Huh?

129
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:21,770
When my mom was in full term...

130
00:10:21,770 --> 00:10:24,840
She went to the rice mill to grind some rice
 and gave birth to me there.

131
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:28,460
She wasn't able to go to the hospital, so a town grandma who helps during birth giving came.

132
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:31,150
And my dad ended up naming me "Jeong Mi."

133
00:10:32,990 --> 00:10:35,700
Why are you laughing at the name of someone's precious son?

134
00:10:35,730 --> 00:10:37,350
I won't laugh.

135
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:41,820
But, Chief Nurse...

136
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:48,260
Rather than taking measures at the level of the association... Could you first...

137
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:49,080
Yes, first...?

138
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:53,790
Couldn't you first clear me of the false accusation
of sexually harassing you?

139
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:55,940
Yes?

140
00:10:58,230 --> 00:11:00,070
Let me think about it first.

141
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:04,140
Eat some.

142
00:11:04,140 --> 00:11:05,840
Eat.

143
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:07,680
I will.

144
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:20,720
Why?

145
00:11:26,470 --> 00:11:28,200
Ouch! (scratchy)

146
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:33,270
Why did you do that?

147
00:11:33,270 --> 00:11:35,300
I'm so thankful about what happened yesterday,

148
00:11:35,340 --> 00:11:38,560
and congratulations on coming out of the police station.

149
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,660
But why a peck on the cheek?

150
00:11:40,710 --> 00:11:44,990
You kissed me when I officially became a resident last time.

151
00:11:44,990 --> 00:11:49,800
It seems like you like it this way that's why I did it too.

152
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:53,140
I don't exactly like it, but it feels weird.

153
00:11:53,770 --> 00:11:55,220
Dr. Park.

154
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:58,390
Don't do that to me. I don't like it.

155
00:11:59,220 --> 00:12:02,210
You received your first kiss from a guy.

156
00:12:02,210 --> 00:12:04,850
How would you know if that's my first kiss or not?

157
00:12:06,930 --> 00:12:10,280
The troublemaker... the Assistant Director is here.

158
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:30,610
What was going to happen has happened, that's all.

159
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:33,070
Rather, just overlooking it is better for us.

160
00:12:33,070 --> 00:12:35,720
But think about all the things Seongwon Foundation went through to cultivate this hospital.

161
00:12:36,650 --> 00:12:38,630
You're worrying over all sorts of things.

162
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:41,860
Just don't think about anything and quietly stay still.

163
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,500
Why?

164
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:48,550
Are you sad about the thought of being a branch director just flew away?

165
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:51,660
You... that was an old story...

166
00:12:51,660 --> 00:12:53,150
Why would you say that?

167
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:55,560
This time, get in the right line.

168
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:58,760
Because West Emerson is precise
 with their personnel management.

169
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:00,770
What line...

170
00:13:00,770 --> 00:13:03,420
A surgeon should be just good at performing surgeries.

171
00:13:03,420 --> 00:13:05,280
I'm going.

172
00:13:07,270 --> 00:13:09,450
What's wrong with him?

173
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:21,810
I thought it was just a rumor but it turns out to be true.

174
00:13:21,810 --> 00:13:24,910
They say the Assistant Director is
 a person from the company taking over.

175
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:29,340
He stabbed the Director and Chairman Lee's back properly.

176
00:13:29,380 --> 00:13:31,700
But then, isn't that a good thing for us?

177
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:35,170
There will be a pediatric surgery center, and later if the whole hospital becomes a children's hospital.

178
00:13:35,190 --> 00:13:36,270
The number of staff will increase, too.

179
00:13:36,270 --> 00:13:39,580
They say they'll convert it to a for-profit hospital,
didn't they, if legislation passes later.

180
00:13:39,580 --> 00:13:41,020
A for-profit hospital?

181
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:42,800
Yes, do you know what that is?

182
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:44,880
Yes, I read it in a news report.

183
00:13:44,880 --> 00:13:46,870
You won't be able to be treated if you don't have money.

184
00:13:46,870 --> 00:13:50,470
Especially the children's treatment fees will become expensive so the parents will have a hard time.

185
00:13:51,090 --> 00:13:52,840
There aren't only bad points.

186
00:13:52,850 --> 00:13:55,900
It's possible to treat patients
 in a somewhat better environment.

187
00:13:55,950 --> 00:14:00,120
Be it a good thing or not, it is not something we could judge.

188
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:04,750
We are just saying this on a doctor's perspective and there should also be the patient's perspective.

189
00:14:05,510 --> 00:14:08,500
Then, the announcement must have been sent out on the messenger because of this.

190
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:11,910
That everyone above assistant professor level is supposed to come to an emergency association meeting.

191
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:16,400
It shouldn't be. It shouldn't really be.

192
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:23,110
Professor, what are you doing not going home?

193
00:14:23,130 --> 00:14:25,850
No need. With just this.

194
00:14:25,890 --> 00:14:29,160
You can't since it's to tiring. You can't do surgeries right now.

195
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:31,480
I can still see patients, so don't worry.

196
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:33,750
Why don't you rest, just like Dr. Cha says.

197
00:14:33,750 --> 00:14:36,090
No need, I said.

198
00:14:36,090 --> 00:14:38,610
These punks talk so much.

199
00:14:41,210 --> 00:14:42,990
He should be resting.

200
00:14:50,570 --> 00:14:52,580
What now?

201
00:14:52,580 --> 00:14:56,050
Is our hospital... really being taken over?

202
00:14:59,780 --> 00:15:02,540
What about the Director and Chairman Lee?

203
00:15:02,870 --> 00:15:05,210
I also don't know that well.

204
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:07,910
What if, after we're taken over, the Director leaves...?

205
00:15:07,910 --> 00:15:09,710
Then I guess there's no need for me to be in this hospital.

206
00:15:09,710 --> 00:15:11,840
Then I will follow you out.

207
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:15,020
Let's think about that later on.

208
00:15:15,020 --> 00:15:17,170
Don't let the juniors get shaken because of this situation.

209
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:21,310
Yes, don't worry.

210
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:30,220
<i> We are sorry to notify you
 that we are unable to handle this case.</i>

211
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:35,340
<i> According to our pediatric department
 the new medical procedure is too risky for this patient.</i>

212
00:15:35,340 --> 00:15:39,520
<i>So we recommend that you discuss this issue with Dr. Cha Yoon Seo </i>

213
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:42,490
<i>at Sungwon University Hospital in South Korea.</i>

214
00:15:42,490 --> 00:15:45,700
<i> Dr Cha has been consulting with us regarding this case</i>

215
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:48,290
<i> and I believe she has found the best possible solution.</i>

216
00:15:48,790 --> 00:15:50,690
Cha Yoon Seo.

217
00:15:57,780 --> 00:16:00,240
I'm pretty sure there's a risk.

218
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:03,620
Should I have researched it more before sending it?

219
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:07,370
I too am not getting the gam* yet.
<i>(feel, sense / persimmon)</i>

220
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:12,330
I too am still not getting the sagwa either.
<i>Sagwa = apple or apology</i>

221
00:16:14,550 --> 00:16:16,010
Ugh...

222
00:16:16,010 --> 00:16:17,440
Why?

223
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:21,010
Did you do that just now to be funny? Gam sagwa?
<i> Gam sagwa = Persimmon apple or feeling of apology</i>

224
00:16:21,850 --> 00:16:23,450
It's not funny, huh?

225
00:16:23,450 --> 00:16:25,160
Yes. (It's not)

226
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:26,910
Sorry.

227
00:16:26,910 --> 00:16:29,860
I ask you to take special care.

228
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:36,290
True, we only issued instructions about the conclusion
 and were not concrete about the process.

229
00:16:36,290 --> 00:16:40,430
Maybe the hospital in Boston also finds it hard.

230
00:16:41,290 --> 00:16:45,820
For now, we will have to request the cooperation of the Taeheung University Hospital professor who examined this child.

231
00:16:45,820 --> 00:16:49,250
Since I'll give him a call, you go and
get the material from him now.

232
00:16:49,290 --> 00:16:51,900
Yes, I will go now.

233
00:16:59,070 --> 00:17:00,510
Hello.

234
00:17:00,530 --> 00:17:01,760
Are you going somewhere?

235
00:17:01,780 --> 00:17:05,330
Yes, I'm going on an errand for Doctor Cha
 to Taeheung University Hospital.

236
00:17:05,390 --> 00:17:07,130
I see...

237
00:17:07,130 --> 00:17:09,470
It's become cold outside suddenly.

238
00:17:09,470 --> 00:17:11,520
You should dress warmly and go out.

239
00:17:12,190 --> 00:17:14,690
I have to go get them at Taebaek.

240
00:17:14,690 --> 00:17:17,550
I didn't bring a single jacket.

241
00:17:20,270 --> 00:17:24,420
Before you do your errand, can you give me just 30 minutes?

242
00:17:35,590 --> 00:17:36,620
Oh...

243
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:38,320
Where are you going?

244
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:41,450
I... I'm alright.

245
00:17:42,330 --> 00:17:43,940
Don't feel burdened.

246
00:17:43,940 --> 00:17:46,590
Just think of it as your older sister buying for you.

247
00:17:47,580 --> 00:17:49,320
Come on.

248
00:17:54,530 --> 00:17:56,240
This is too wide.

249
00:17:59,380 --> 00:18:01,680
The Director told me...

250
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,900
not to be indebted to strangers.

251
00:18:04,900 --> 00:18:07,210
Am I such a stranger?

252
00:18:18,980 --> 00:18:21,250
Oh. This is nice.

253
00:18:22,220 --> 00:18:23,800
It's handsome, isn't it?

254
00:18:28,850 --> 00:18:31,070
It suits you well.

255
00:18:32,110 --> 00:18:34,960
Oh my! Didn't I take so much of your time?

256
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:36,810
No.

257
00:18:36,810 --> 00:18:39,250
Thank you so much.

