521
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:37,270
I always make a ruckus saying I'll handle it by myself,

522
00:37:37,270 --> 00:37:39,120
but I never do one thing properly.

523
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:41,300
You do make a ruckus,

524
00:37:42,150 --> 00:37:44,100
but there are more times that you do things properly.

525
00:37:45,210 --> 00:37:46,780
Kim Do Han!

526
00:37:47,730 --> 00:37:48,820
What?

527
00:37:48,820 --> 00:37:52,370
Why are you acting so much like a lover all of a sudden?

528
00:37:52,370 --> 00:37:55,400
Of course I'm your lover, am I an
adolescent from your neighborhood?

529
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:58,540
It's because I'm getting scared that
you're being like this all of a sudden.

530
00:37:59,610 --> 00:38:02,140
I'm afraid that you'll become cold again after being like this.

531
00:38:03,990 --> 00:38:07,230
I'm afraid that you'll be alone again.

532
00:38:08,130 --> 00:38:10,780
Dr. Park Si On said that.

533
00:38:10,780 --> 00:38:15,880
That you always eat alone and you don't smile that much, either.

534
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:19,490
I was like that, too.

535
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:24,960
I wish all of the good memories would return soon.

536
00:38:25,640 --> 00:38:30,430
At the time when I liked all people ...

537
00:38:30,430 --> 00:38:32,390
Those warm memories?

538
00:39:08,630 --> 00:39:13,370
I would like to tell you my opinions about my son's surgery.

539
00:39:14,450 --> 00:39:16,290
Among both of you,

540
00:39:17,980 --> 00:39:20,030
one of you go to Boston, please.

541
00:39:25,110 --> 00:39:27,790
I understand what you're trying to say,

542
00:39:27,790 --> 00:39:30,110
but the people over there still won't perform the surgery.

543
00:39:30,810 --> 00:39:35,380
And we are not participants. We only
have the right to become simple advisers.

544
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:40,770
Please bring him to our hospital.

545
00:39:42,150 --> 00:39:46,550
We know very well that you don't trust
 our Pediatric Surgery Department.

546
00:39:46,550 --> 00:39:48,690
The choice is up to you, Assistant Director.

547
00:39:48,690 --> 00:39:52,890
It's not that I can't trust you. It's just that
 I trust that side a little bit more.

548
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:56,990
Seongwon University Hospital, the Pediatric
 Surgery Department's capabilities,

549
00:39:56,990 --> 00:39:58,820
I know them better than anyone.

550
00:39:58,820 --> 00:40:00,450
However,

551
00:40:01,730 --> 00:40:05,350
it's a bit early for me to trust you.

552
00:40:07,290 --> 00:40:10,580
That's why I wanted to reform it.

553
00:40:10,580 --> 00:40:14,450
To create a hospital that I was more one
hundred percent sure about than anything else.

554
00:40:15,640 --> 00:40:17,530
Do you think a patient's trust

555
00:40:18,430 --> 00:40:21,980
can be gained by only investment and reform?

556
00:40:23,070 --> 00:40:26,020
What good does it do to have a good system and facility?

557
00:40:26,020 --> 00:40:30,460
If we can't do surgeries for them at the most needed time?

558
00:41:56,310 --> 00:42:00,070
<i>We too have no intention of performing a surgery without the guardian's trust.</i>

559
00:42:00,070 --> 00:42:02,250
<i>I believe this is beyond our control,</i>

560
00:42:02,250 --> 00:42:04,080
<i>so I sincerely wish you luck.</i>

561
00:42:08,460 --> 00:42:10,500
Hello.

562
00:42:11,660 --> 00:42:14,530
Yes, hello.

563
00:42:14,530 --> 00:42:18,130
Assistant Director. You're bad.

564
00:42:19,650 --> 00:42:21,650
I heard.

565
00:42:21,650 --> 00:42:23,020
That you're trying to convert

566
00:42:23,020 --> 00:42:27,210
our hospital into a for-profit hospital.

567
00:42:27,210 --> 00:42:29,660
I also know what that means.

568
00:42:29,660 --> 00:42:32,120
It will make the children and parents' lives more difficult.

569
00:42:32,120 --> 00:42:35,820
If they have no money, they can't even get a proper surgery.

570
00:42:40,240 --> 00:42:42,690
There are two sides to everything.

571
00:42:42,690 --> 00:42:46,060
I believe the matter at hand is not much different, Doctor.

572
00:42:46,060 --> 00:42:48,560
That is not so.

573
00:42:48,560 --> 00:42:51,090
Even if we have good equipment and a good facility,

574
00:42:51,090 --> 00:42:54,190
if the patients can't come, there's no use.

575
00:42:54,190 --> 00:42:57,400
It gets sadder if they die because they can't come.

576
00:42:57,400 --> 00:43:00,450
When the chance to live gets taken away,

577
00:43:00,450 --> 00:43:02,810
it gets even sadder.

578
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:26,040
Say it again.

579
00:43:27,110 --> 00:43:28,410
In Hae.

580
00:43:28,410 --> 00:43:31,040
This means the donor of my small intestine is

581
00:43:31,040 --> 00:43:34,020
you.

582
00:43:34,020 --> 00:43:37,640
Then it means you're giving me yours.

583
00:43:37,640 --> 00:43:39,260
They say it's the safest way.

584
00:43:39,260 --> 00:43:41,660
Are you crazy, Unni?

585
00:43:41,660 --> 00:43:47,170
You worked your butt off for me, and now you're giving me your intestine?

586
00:43:47,170 --> 00:43:49,600
I'm okay.

587
00:43:49,650 --> 00:43:50,450
So, In Hae...

588
00:43:50,550 --> 00:43:52,050
Forget it!

589
00:43:52,080 --> 00:43:54,870
I don't need a surgery or anything.

590
00:43:54,870 --> 00:43:59,790
I'm just going to die! I'm just going to die!

591
00:43:59,790 --> 00:44:02,890
In Hae! In Hae!

592
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:05,910
In Hae!

593
00:44:07,050 --> 00:44:09,400
In Hae!

594
00:44:36,060 --> 00:44:37,640
Don't come.

595
00:44:37,640 --> 00:44:40,660
I'm going to be here alone.

596
00:44:40,660 --> 00:44:41,570
In Hae.

597
00:44:41,570 --> 00:44:43,850
I told you not to come.

598
00:44:57,450 --> 00:44:59,430
Why did you

599
00:44:59,430 --> 00:45:02,970
not tell me in advance?

600
00:45:04,940 --> 00:45:06,900
I, too,

601
00:45:07,380 --> 00:45:10,360
thought there was some other donor.

602
00:45:14,820 --> 00:45:16,670
Look.

603
00:45:17,100 --> 00:45:19,660
It's not an urgent surgery,

604
00:45:19,660 --> 00:45:22,100
so if you would wait just a little more...

605
00:45:22,100 --> 00:45:24,180
Please don't say anything.

606
00:46:01,430 --> 00:46:02,630
Professor.

607
00:46:02,630 --> 00:46:05,120
They say In Hae's surgery has been scheduled.

608
00:46:05,120 --> 00:46:06,660
Why was In Hae's surgery scheduled?

609
00:46:06,660 --> 00:46:09,530
They say Chief Kim from HPB scheduled it.

610
00:46:09,530 --> 00:46:11,380
Chief Kim?

611
00:46:11,380 --> 00:46:13,680
Why didn't you tell us anything?

612
00:46:13,680 --> 00:46:16,070
Na In Young wanted me to keep it secret.

613
00:46:16,070 --> 00:46:18,690
Then you should've told us at least right before you scheduled the surgery.

614
00:46:18,690 --> 00:46:21,460
You did find out eventually.

615
00:46:21,460 --> 00:46:22,870
In Hae.

616
00:46:22,980 --> 00:46:24,530
She's a patient whom we have been continuously monitoring.

617
00:46:24,530 --> 00:46:25,420
So?

618
00:46:25,430 --> 00:46:28,270
We must participate in the surgery as well.

619
00:46:30,930 --> 00:46:32,240
Intestine transplant.

620
00:46:32,240 --> 00:46:33,500
You don't have much experiece of it.

621
00:46:33,500 --> 00:46:35,760
I don't have much, but I've never failed at it, either.

622
00:46:35,760 --> 00:46:38,550
You can't do that when you've only done a few.

623
00:46:38,550 --> 00:46:40,710
I have to be in full charge of this surgery.

624
00:46:40,710 --> 00:46:42,400
If I have your department in it,

625
00:46:42,400 --> 00:46:44,870
I'll get distracted, so it can't happen.

626
00:46:45,530 --> 00:46:48,440
In Hae's condition is different from any other short gut syndrome.

627
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:52,380
Intestine barely exists, so we need to come up with another surgery method until right before the transplant.

628
00:46:52,380 --> 00:46:54,870
Are you lecturing at me?

629
00:46:56,550 --> 00:46:59,590
That I might do the surgery without even knowing that...

630
00:46:59,590 --> 00:47:01,960
Are you worried?

631
00:47:01,960 --> 00:47:04,350
I'll take care of it on my own,

632
00:47:04,350 --> 00:47:06,590
so you just stay put.

633
00:47:20,200 --> 00:47:22,040
What were you thinking coming here so thoughtlessly?

634
00:47:22,040 --> 00:47:23,460
I'm sorry.

635
00:47:23,460 --> 00:47:25,510
We had no options over there,

636
00:47:25,510 --> 00:47:27,930
and Joon Yeong wanted to come to Korea, too.

637
00:47:27,930 --> 00:47:31,570
Then you should've called me in advance
 at the airport, not here.

638
00:47:48,150 --> 00:47:49,150
Dad.

639
00:47:49,170 --> 00:47:50,530
Yes.

640
00:47:51,550 --> 00:47:53,050
You must be tired coming all the way here.

641
00:47:53,070 --> 00:47:55,360
Dad.

642
00:47:56,070 --> 00:47:59,910
I heard they could cure me here.

643
00:48:02,620 --> 00:48:05,350
I hope it will happen for sure.

644
00:48:06,470 --> 00:48:09,560
So I can play baseball again.

645
00:48:09,650 --> 00:48:10,940
Yes.

646
00:48:12,850 --> 00:48:15,060
I'll make that happen.

647
00:48:38,670 --> 00:48:40,730
I'm going to have him admitted just for the time being.

648
00:48:40,730 --> 00:48:43,110
Until I find other alternative.

649
00:48:43,110 --> 00:48:45,020
Please do as you like.

650
00:48:45,020 --> 00:48:47,390
Thank you for your understanding.

651
00:48:47,390 --> 00:48:50,260
Let me ask just one question.

652
00:48:50,260 --> 00:48:53,140
I thought, by observing our pediatric surgeries until now,

653
00:48:53,140 --> 00:48:55,250
you would have more than enough reasons

654
00:48:55,250 --> 00:48:57,240
to know our ability.

655
00:48:57,240 --> 00:48:59,240
You even told us you trusted us.

656
00:49:00,620 --> 00:49:04,050
I don't understand why you distrust us now despite all that.

657
00:49:04,050 --> 00:49:06,040
The reason is simple.

658
00:49:06,040 --> 00:49:08,020
Because

659
00:49:08,020 --> 00:49:09,980
I'm his father.

660
00:49:10,720 --> 00:49:14,970
There's no father in the world

661
00:49:15,870 --> 00:49:18,210
who would put his own child at the risk of uncertainty.

662
00:49:18,540 --> 00:49:20,180
Honey.

663
00:49:20,180 --> 00:49:22,510
You don't say anything.

664
00:49:30,660 --> 00:49:32,610
Are you

665
00:49:32,610 --> 00:49:36,110
Dr. Cha Yoon Seo?

666
00:49:36,110 --> 00:49:38,450
Do you know me?

667
00:49:38,450 --> 00:49:39,630
Yes.

668
00:49:39,630 --> 00:49:44,930
My mom showed me the email you sent her.

669
00:49:44,930 --> 00:49:48,270
A way to do surgery.

670
00:49:48,270 --> 00:49:49,740
I see.

671
00:49:49,740 --> 00:49:53,720
You're much prettier than I had imagined.

672
00:49:55,380 --> 00:49:56,290
Thanks.

673
00:49:57,050 --> 00:50:00,950
Doctor, you will do my operation, right?

674
00:50:02,840 --> 00:50:05,040
Please promise me.

675
00:50:05,040 --> 00:50:11,540
After seeing your letter, I pestered
my mom to come back to Korea.

676
00:50:25,540 --> 00:50:27,250
Why is everyone set on his or her way?

677
00:50:27,250 --> 00:50:29,490
If there's a better solution they should pick that one.

678
00:50:29,490 --> 00:50:31,450
Please calm down.

679
00:50:31,460 --> 00:50:35,520
If something happens to the kid, each will try
to avoid blame or harm probably.

680
00:50:35,570 --> 00:50:40,490
There's nothing we can do. Everyone thinks
 his or her choice is the right one.

681
00:50:49,900 --> 00:50:55,170
No matter how much I learn about the world, there are too many hard things.

682
00:50:57,000 --> 00:51:01,880
There are hard thing for me too. The older I get...

683
00:51:03,010 --> 00:51:08,030
I don't know why people only believe in their thoughts and not listen to others.

684
00:51:08,660 --> 00:51:11,240
A disease does not hurt the person...

685
00:51:11,240 --> 00:51:14,250
A person hurts the person more, I think.

686
00:51:14,280 --> 00:51:17,060
Not even a doctor can fix that.

687
00:51:18,680 --> 00:51:22,870
For a virus, there's a vaccine and for a tumor, there's an anti-tumor agent.

688
00:51:22,910 --> 00:51:27,880
There is no remedy for a person that hurts others.

689
00:51:27,950 --> 00:51:32,550
You're right but the only remedy is another person.

690
00:51:33,320 --> 00:51:38,100
I wish doctor could fix diseases and people.

691
00:51:38,100 --> 00:51:40,450
You are doing that.

692
00:51:41,770 --> 00:51:45,210
All those children with wounds that we saw...

693
00:51:45,210 --> 00:51:47,960
They all got discharged because their hearts were healed.

694
00:51:47,980 --> 00:51:53,710
Not because of the treatments but because you reduced their pain by giving them love.

695
00:51:55,320 --> 00:52:00,420
Love... reduced... pain?

696
00:52:00,460 --> 00:52:03,230
That's why you're a good doctor.

697
00:52:04,380 --> 00:52:08,440
I still don't know what a good doctor is.

698
00:52:08,470 --> 00:52:11,530
A good person.

699
00:52:11,530 --> 00:52:15,410
I think a good person becomes a good doctor.

700
00:52:15,420 --> 00:52:20,300
Oh! That's why you're a good doctor.

701
00:52:20,310 --> 00:52:24,240
No. I'm still a doctor who's about to become good... or not.

702
00:52:24,860 --> 00:52:28,830
No, you're wrong. If I say you're wrong then you're wrong.

703
00:52:30,750 --> 00:52:35,020
Are you my fan-club president? Your praise is too much.

704
00:52:35,020 --> 00:52:38,140
I'm your bba, a "do-anything-for-you fan". Cha Yoon Seo's bba (die hard fan).

705
00:52:38,140 --> 00:52:42,850
Stop spending so much time on the internet. You speak more and more weird language as the day goes by.

706
00:52:57,480 --> 00:52:59,910
Dr. Park, haven't you seen In Hae?

707
00:52:59,910 --> 00:53:02,050
I didn't. Did she go somewhere?

708
00:53:02,150 --> 00:53:06,350
A short while ago, she must have come to her hospital room and, while I was not around, changed into her clothes and gone out.

709
00:53:06,350 --> 00:53:08,870
I will go outside right now to look for her.

710
00:53:24,280 --> 00:53:26,330
In Hae.

711
00:53:28,050 --> 00:53:31,220
Why are you here?

712
00:53:31,220 --> 00:53:34,530
Did you come out as you pleased again?

713
00:53:34,560 --> 00:53:38,630
You shouldn't be here.
Let's hurry back into the hospital.

714
00:53:38,660 --> 00:53:41,010
I don't want to.

715
00:53:42,210 --> 00:53:46,470
Today, I just really don't want to be at the hospital.

716
00:53:55,550 --> 00:53:58,960
Yes. I understand.

717
00:53:58,970 --> 00:54:03,330
Dr. Cha has taken her and will bring her tomorrow.

718
00:54:05,910 --> 00:54:08,900
Don't worry too much, Miss In Yeong.

719
00:54:24,140 --> 00:54:26,490
Ta da!

720
00:54:30,900 --> 00:54:34,200
That's the bathroom. Go take a bath and disinfect yourself.

721
00:54:34,210 --> 00:54:35,670
Inside there's a disinfecting solution.

722
00:54:35,670 --> 00:54:38,390
Yes.

723
00:54:50,760 --> 00:54:53,600
Excuse me, Respected Elder Sister.

724
00:54:53,600 --> 00:54:55,820
Yes, Doctor?

725
00:54:55,840 --> 00:55:00,080
Dr. Cha will look after her very well.

726
00:55:00,090 --> 00:55:03,750
Yes, of course, she would.

727
00:55:03,750 --> 00:55:07,540
In Hae should be mad and hurt now but...

728
00:55:07,560 --> 00:55:10,370
She will understand your heart.

729
00:55:10,370 --> 00:55:13,070
In Hae seems more mature than me.

730
00:55:13,070 --> 00:55:15,430
She is a child with a large heart.

731
00:55:17,370 --> 00:55:20,240
And, Respected Elder Sister...

732
00:55:20,260 --> 00:55:23,470
It's kinda weird being called Respected Elder Sister just...

733
00:55:23,510 --> 00:55:25,830
Please just call me In Yeong.

734
00:55:25,870 --> 00:55:27,980
Ah, yes.

735
00:55:27,980 --> 00:55:31,330
In Yeong... excuse me but...

736
00:55:31,370 --> 00:55:35,520
Dr. Han Jin Wook likes you a lot.

737
00:55:37,300 --> 00:55:41,050
He sleeps above me in the night-duty room bunk bed.

738
00:55:41,070 --> 00:55:43,190
He rolls over every night.

739
00:55:43,220 --> 00:55:45,770
He's too loud for me to fall asleep.

740
00:55:45,770 --> 00:55:49,300
So I also stay up all night.

741
00:55:51,020 --> 00:55:55,350
I thought I was the biggest idiot inside this hospital but..

742
00:55:55,370 --> 00:55:59,180
Han sunbae was behind me.

743
00:55:59,220 --> 00:56:02,690
He's really, really a dummie.

744
00:56:02,700 --> 00:56:05,590
Dr. Han told me this:

745
00:56:05,600 --> 00:56:12,120
"There's no qualifications necessary to love someone, and if you love that person sincerely without any condition,

746
00:56:12,140 --> 00:56:16,090
you develop the qualifications necessary
 for just that person."

747
00:56:18,240 --> 00:56:22,840
I, Respected Elder Sister, that is, In Yeong,

748
00:56:22,840 --> 00:56:27,020
would give Han Sunbae a certificate of qualification.

749
00:56:27,050 --> 00:56:32,360
So that he can carry in around in his heart, not his wallet.

750
00:56:36,470 --> 00:56:42,180
Have you not thought about how your sister
would be happier to let you get your surgery?

751
00:56:42,180 --> 00:56:44,190
Why would she be happy?

752
00:56:44,190 --> 00:56:47,930
She can't even fall in love or get married.

753
00:56:47,930 --> 00:56:51,210
No. She can do everything.

754
00:56:51,210 --> 00:56:53,650
It's not that serious a surgery.

755
00:56:53,660 --> 00:56:56,740
Believe what your doc is saying.

756
00:56:59,000 --> 00:57:03,330
How do you and your sister have such kind hearts?

757
00:57:03,350 --> 00:57:05,270
-- Doc.
 -- Hmm?

758
00:57:05,580 --> 00:57:09,410
But... didn't you refuse Dr. Park's confession?

759
00:57:09,410 --> 00:57:10,510
What?

760
00:57:10,510 --> 00:57:12,850
Because the rose is hung over there.

761
00:57:12,850 --> 00:57:17,250
If you hadn't accepted his confession, you
would have thrown it away. Strange.

762
00:57:18,440 --> 00:57:20,780
How do you know that?

763
00:57:20,780 --> 00:57:25,560
Doc Park said he liked someone, so I counseled him.

764
00:57:25,590 --> 00:57:29,770
But he wouldn't say who he liked no matter what.

765
00:57:29,790 --> 00:57:33,680
Then, in your cell phone, I saw that.

766
00:57:33,710 --> 00:57:36,660
That's the confession method I told him about.

767
00:57:36,680 --> 00:57:38,690
Really!

768
00:57:38,690 --> 00:57:40,590
Why are you that embarrassed?

769
00:57:40,640 --> 00:57:44,060
No, I'm not embarrassed.

770
00:57:48,750 --> 00:57:51,350
- Why?!
- Nothing.

771
00:57:53,040 --> 00:57:58,620
Just. Because he confessed so earnestly,
I couldn't ignore it.

772
00:57:58,660 --> 00:58:03,380
Then, it's not because you accepted his confession that you hung up the rose, but...

773
00:58:03,390 --> 00:58:06,790
you hung it up to mean that you're not ignoring his feelings?

774
00:58:06,810 --> 00:58:08,140
Yep.

775
00:58:09,370 --> 00:58:11,940
I'm acknowledging him as an adult.

776
00:58:11,970 --> 00:58:15,100
I thought...

777
00:58:15,130 --> 00:58:20,830
Doc Park... is a very good man.

778
00:58:20,850 --> 00:58:22,840
I know.

779
00:58:22,850 --> 00:58:28,750
I... would like it if all the good men in this world wouldn't get hurt.

